<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-12-0845 </DOCNO><TEXT>In 1982 Shell and Heineken entered into a basic agreement on investingand exploiting a cogeneration installation for the Heineken productiondepartment in Zoeterwoude, Netherlands. For this purpose the Energy ConversionCompany Zoeterwoude (ECMZ) was founded. The ECMZ purpose is to conversegas and water into electric power and steam. Before realizing the constructionof a cogeneration plant a feasibility study was done, of which the resultsare given. Details of the cogeneration installation are explained withthe help of illustrations. The installation is in operation for morethan two years and in technical respect not disappointing. Financial-economicalthe project did not come up to expectations as a consequence of decreasein energy prices in 1985.</TEXT></DOC>